### Test Events API - Event Assignment System
### Make sure to replace YOUR_ORG_ID with your actual organization ID

### 1. Test GET /api/events (should return empty array initially)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLERK_TOKEN

### 2. Test GET /api/events?filter=my (should return empty array for assigned events)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events?filter=my
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLERK_TOKEN

### 3. Test POST /api/events (create a new event with assigned members)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/events
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLERK_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Test Event - Team Meeting",
  "description": "Weekly team sync meeting",
  "event_type": "business",
  "start_date": "2024-01-15T10:00:00Z",
  "end_date": "2024-01-15T11:00:00Z",
  "location": "Conference Room A",
  "assigned_members": ["USER_ID_1", "USER_ID_2"]
}

### 4. Test GET /api/events/[id] (get specific event)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events/EVENT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLERK_TOKEN

### 5. Test POST /api/events/[id]/assign (assign members to event)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/events/EVENT_ID_HERE/assign
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLERK_TOKEN

{
  "memberIds": ["USER_ID_3", "USER_ID_4"]
}

### 6. Test PUT /api/events/[id] (update event)
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/events/EVENT_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLERK_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Updated Event Name",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "assigned_members": ["USER_ID_1", "USER_ID_2", "USER_ID_3"]
}

### 7. Test GET /api/events?filter=my (should now return assigned events)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/events?filter=my
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLERK_TOKEN

### 8. Test DELETE /api/events/[id] (delete event)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/events/EVENT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_CLERK_TOKEN
